[3] New South Wales
Date: Wed 27 Jul 2011
From: Storm Stanford <storm.stanford@gmail.com> [edited]


Updates and access to previous editions are available at
http://www.agriculture.nsw.gov.au/info/hendra

Current situation
-----------------
A 5th horse has died from Hendra virus on a property near Mullumbimby,
on the New South Wales North Coast.

The property has been quarantined and movement restrictions are in
place for all horses and domestic animals, including dogs and cats.

There are 8 other horses on the quarantined property. One is showing
signs of illness but has been initially tested negative for Hendra.
The others are currently showing no signs of illness.

There are 3 cats and 2 dogs on the property -- all will be assessed in
line with NSW DPI's [Department of Primary Industries] policy for
companion animals.

The Mullumbimby area property is the 4th in NSW affected by Hendra
virus after properties at Wollongbar, Macksville, and Lismore were
quarantined earlier in the month [July 2011].

Hendra in NSW snapshot (since 30 Jun 2011):
- 4 properties have been confirmed positive for the Hendra virus
- 87 properties have been confirmed as negative for the Hendra virus,
with further confirmatory antibody testing still underway on some
properties
- Awaiting results for 2 samples.

Hendra virus and companion animals
----------------------------------
NSW DPI's policy is to routinely test all companion animals that are
assessed as having had or been likely to have had close contact with
an infected horse.

All animals at infected NSW properties have been assessed as being low
risk.

--
Storm Stanford
<storm.stanford@gmail.com>

